<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,554,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,591,617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[333,433,592,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kupiuka" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[333,433,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Kupiuka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the remaining genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1054,592,618]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heliophaninae">Heliophaninae</taxonomicName>
by having the glandular portion of the wall of the copulation duct developed into what appears to be an extra spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1292,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,387,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,381,1878]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Kupiuka extratheca sp. nov. 1 male habitus; 2 – 3 left male palp, (2 ventral, 3 retrolateral); 4 – 5 male palpal femur (4 retrolateral, 5 prolateral); 6 epigyne, ventral view; 7 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198309/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1305,1337,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,955,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,943,1470]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 16. Kupiuka taruman sp. nov. 15 epigyne, ventral view; 16 vulva, dorsal view. Scale: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198312/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1349,1382,629,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,199,1135]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1146]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Kupiuka heteropicta sp. nov. 17 – 19 left male palp (17 ventral, 18 retrolateral, 19 ventroretrolateral); 20 male palpal femur, prolateral view; 21 epigyne, ventral view; 22 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198313/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<number box="[1349,1382,629,655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,554,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,355,666,692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Description.</emphasis>
The genus includes small jumping spiders (
<quantity box="[899,995,666,692]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4mm</quantity>
) with granulose areas on the lateral surfaces of the anterior carapace and three modified setae on the distal prolateral portion of femur I for stridulation, as those described for species of 
<taxonomicName box="[680,779,741,766]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,779,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<collectingCountry box="[680,779,741,766]" name="Switzerland" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Helvetia</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[835,949,741,766]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Matagaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,949,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Matagaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[1009,1282,741,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2008) Revision of Helvetia (Araneae: Salticidae: Heliophaninae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 25, 139 - 147." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 
<number box="[1220,1282,741,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 
<number box="[1343,1387,741,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[151,343,778,804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Freitas, G. C. C. (2007) Spiders from Fernando de Noronha, Brazil. Part II. Proposal of a new genus and description of three new species of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 24, 771 - 776." type="journal article" year="2007">
Ruiz 
<emphasis box="[214,266,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[281,343,778,804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 
<number box="[406,453,778,804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
); bodies are slightly elongate and flattened; chelicerae with two teeth on promargin and one on retromargin; male palps with a prolateral depression on femora; glandular portion of the wall of the copulation duct of the epigyne seems to be developed into an extra spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1135,1210,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,387,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,381,1878]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Kupiuka extratheca sp. nov. 1 male habitus; 2 – 3 left male palp, (2 ventral, 3 retrolateral); 4 – 5 male palpal femur (4 retrolateral, 5 prolateral); 6 epigyne, ventral view; 7 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198309/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1222,1253,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,955,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,943,1470]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 16. Kupiuka taruman sp. nov. 15 epigyne, ventral view; 16 vulva, dorsal view. Scale: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198312/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1266,1299,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,199,1135]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1146]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Kupiuka heteropicta sp. nov. 17 – 19 left male palp (17 ventral, 18 retrolateral, 19 ventroretrolateral); 20 male palpal femur, prolateral view; 21 epigyne, ventral view; 22 vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198313/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<number box="[1266,1299,853,879]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
), while true spermathecae are not differentiated in girth. This apparent extra spermatheca is probably homologous to the flower-shaped gland present in dendryphantines (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Maddison" box="[802,996,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Maddison, W. P. (1996) Pelegrina and other jumping spiders formerly placed in the genus Metaphidippus (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, l 54, 215 - 368." type="journal article" year="1996">
Maddison 
<number box="[931,996,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1009,1057,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="225.0">225</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1120,1135,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
) and long, chimney-like structures (also treated by some authors as “scent gland”, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berry" box="[915,1228,965,991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Berry, J. W. &amp; Proszynski, J. (2001) Description of Hakka, a new genus of jumping spider (Araneae, Salticidae) from Hawaii and East Asia. The Journal of Arachnology, 29, 201 - 204." type="journal article" year="2001">
Berry &amp; Prószyński 
<number box="[1166,1228,965,991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) present in other salticids, such as amycines and sitticines (Amycoida) or even in 
<taxonomicName authority="Berry &amp; Proszynski, 2001" authorityName="Berry &amp; Proszynski" authorityYear="2001" box="[979,1401,1002,1028]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hakka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1060,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Hakka</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berry" box="[1069,1401,1002,1028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Berry, J. W. &amp; Proszynski, J. (2001) Description of Hakka, a new genus of jumping spider (Araneae, Salticidae) from Hawaii and East Asia. The Journal of Arachnology, 29, 201 - 204." type="journal article" year="2001">
Berry &amp; Prószyński, 
<number box="[1339,1401,1002,1028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1902" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,436,1040,1066]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pseudicius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Pseudicius</emphasis>
Simon, 
<number box="[377,436,1040,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1902.0">1902</number>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[450,628,1040,1066]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heliophaninae">Heliophaninae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
